The paper discusses the evaluation of three representative data center systems based on BigDataBench, which is a benchmark suite for benchmarking and ranking systems running big data applications. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category, as well as the Databases (cs.DB) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the construction of data center systems, which could fall under the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also mentions the consideration of application-level characteristics, which could relate to the Artificial Intelligence and Robotics (cs.AR) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the performance and energy consumption of hardware, which could relate to the Computer Engineering (cs.CE) sub-category.
